The paper deals with the problem of scheduling data communication within a data center and between data centers, which is a core problem in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and heuristics, which are common techniques in the field of algorithms and complexity, making cs.AL (Computational Complexity) another likely category. The paper also involves the study of graphs and their properties, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with the scheduling of data flows, which is a core problem in distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely category as well.
